windows and created a vortex.

33:36.033 --> 33:37.534
Okay.

33:37.534 --> 33:39.534
We'll ignore the fact
that you used "vortex"

33:39.534 --> 33:40.667
correctly in a sentence.

33:40.667 --> 33:41.868
But I just wanna point out

33:41.868 --> 33:43.033
that we have about 40 people

33:43.033 --> 33:44.501
waiting on a cliff someplace

33:44.501 --> 33:45.734
to spread Lou's ashes,

33:45.734 --> 33:47.534
which we no longer have
enough of.

33:47.534 --> 33:50.167
Yeah, like this isn't even
Lou's leg.

33:50.167 --> 33:53.133
I say we burn up Mike
and put his ashes in a box.

33:53.133 --> 33:54.534
First of all,
we don't have time.

33:54.534 --> 33:56.400
Second of all,
we don't have an accelerant.

33:56.400 --> 33:58.501
Otherwise
he'd already be on fire.

33:58.501 --> 34:02.234
Maybe we could get some dirt
and mix it up in there.

34:02.234 --> 34:04.834
What did I just say? I said
we have to spread his ashes.

34:04.834 --> 34:06.834
We have to spread them out
lightly on the breeze

34:06.834 --> 34:08.033
so that they disappear,

34:08.033 --> 34:10.567
not land in a goddamn clump
two feet away.

34:10.567 --> 34:11.567
Oh, I got a better idea.

34:11.567 --> 34:12.567
Why don't we mix in

34:12.567 --> 34:13.900
some hay and grass and shit?

34:13.900 --> 34:14.934
And tell people what?

34:14.934 --> 34:16.833
That he believed
in reincarnation,

34:16.833 --> 34:18.833
and he came back
as a goddamn bird's nest?

34:20.534 --> 34:21.634
SHAWN:
Listen up, guys.

34:21.634 --> 34:23.100
We passed a store
a few miles back.

34:23.100 --> 34:24.833
I'm sure we can find
something there.

34:24.833 --> 34:26.467
Oh, yeah, maybe
they sell Lou Helper.

34:26.467 --> 34:27.667
You got a better suggestion?

34:27.667 --> 34:29.132
You know what?
It's not a bad idea.

34:29.132 --> 34:30.534
We're gonna go back
to the store.

34:30.534 --> 34:32.434
We're gonna find something
light and fluffy

34:32.434 --> 34:33.434
that we can mix in.

34:33.434 --> 34:34.701
In the meantime,

34:34.701 --> 34:36.367
we're gonna need
all the Lou we can get.

34:36.367 --> 34:40.199
Including that ass-crack ash.
Break it out right now.

34:40.199 --> 34:42.333
Right. Like I'm just gonna
drop trou right here

34:42.333 --> 34:43.900
on the side of the road?

34:52.000 --> 34:54.367
You know, there's a lot of ways
I wanted to remember Lou.

34:54.367 --> 34:55.601
This is not one of them.

34:55.601 --> 34:57.534
[SEAN GRUNTING]

35:01.200 --> 35:02.801
[SIREN BLARING]

35:02.801 --> 35:04.400
Oh, sh-sh-shit!

35:04.400 --> 35:06.100
Guys, hey, guys.

35:06.100 --> 35:08.701
Tell this guy I'm not taking
a shit. Guys, Hey! Hi.

35:08.701 --> 35:10.534
Sir--
I'm not pooping.

35:10.534 --> 35:12.767
Step away from the box,
please.

35:19.634 --> 35:21.968
MICK:
"And the old earth must die.

35:21.968 --> 35:24.000
"So let the warm winds range

35:24.000 --> 35:26.334
"and the blue wave
beat the shore.

35:26.334 --> 35:30.234
"For eve and morn, ye will
never see through eternity.

35:30.234 --> 35:32.534
"All things were born.

35:32.534 --> 35:37.968
Ye will come never more,
for all things must die."

35:37.968 --> 35:41.734
Before we release Lou's remains
to the wind and the sea,

35:41.734 --> 35:43.901
let's take this final moment
to share any thoughts

35:43.901 --> 35:47.834
we might have had about him
or what he meant to us.

35:47.834 --> 35:49.334
Anybody?

35:51.434 --> 35:54.434
He was kind.
That's what I'm gonna remember.

35:54.434 --> 35:56.567
Lou, he always treated me
with respect.

35:57.567 --> 35:58.734
He never treated me like

35:58.734 --> 36:02.133
I was his best friend's
messed-up sister.

36:02.133 --> 36:05.934
I wasn't someone he had to
endure, you know?

36:05.934 --> 36:08.968
He always treated me
like I was a lady.

36:08.968 --> 36:10.501
I'm gonna miss that.

36:12.534 --> 36:16.667
He was a great lieutenant.
Truly.

36:18.334 --> 36:20.634
I'm gonna be wearing
a blue shirt pretty soon,

36:20.634 --> 36:23.567
but I'll never be half
the leader that Lou was.

36:26.767 --> 36:28.033
He taught me a lot.

36:29.567 --> 36:32.200
I'm gonna miss him.

36:34.067 --> 36:36.067
He had a big heart.

36:36.067 --> 36:38.834
He loved life.

36:38.834 --> 36:40.300
And cake.

36:40.300 --> 36:41.434
[ALL CHUCKLE]

36:43.667 --> 36:47.701
He was a hell of a firefighter.
God knows he loved to eat.

36:47.701 --> 36:48.968
[CHUCKLES]

36:52.434 --> 36:54.834
He had an encyclopedic
memory of porn.

36:54.834 --> 36:56.834
Well, you couldn't
stump the guy.

36:56.834 --> 36:58.033
Lithuanian midget porn?

36:58.033 --> 36:59.567
He'd rattle off
half a dozen titles

36:59.567 --> 37:01.200
without batting an eye.

37:01.200 --> 37:02.634
Uncanny.

37:04.000 --> 37:06.934
Well, he took
my "big heart" line.

37:06.934 --> 37:09.901
Yeah. This was my fault.

37:11.033 --> 37:12.701
Anybody else?

37:16.534 --> 37:18.033
Tom?

37:19.467 --> 37:20.467
Well, I...

37:20.467 --> 37:22.033
[CLEARS THROAT]

37:23.133 --> 37:25.067
Don't really have a lot to say.

37:27.400 --> 37:33.033
But, fortunately,
Lou does.

37:33.033 --> 37:35.667
He left this letter, uh,
in my locker

37:35.667 --> 37:38.033
with specific instructions
on the front for it

37:38.033 --> 37:42.267
not to be opened
until after he died.

37:42.267 --> 37:45.467
And unlike some people we know,

37:45.467 --> 37:49.567
I actually obeyed
the instructions.

37:49.567 --> 37:53.701
So, here goes.

37:55.534 --> 37:56.534
"Dear Tom."

37:56.534 --> 37:58.167
[CLEARS THROAT]

37:58.167 --> 38:01.334
"If you're reading this,
it probably means I'm dead.

38:02.534 --> 38:04.100
"It might have come
as a shock to you,

38:04.100 --> 38:05.901
"but I'll tell you now.

38:05.901 --> 38:08.767
"I was living on borrowed time.

38:08.767 --> 38:11.467
"My heart went bad a while back.

38:11.467 --> 38:13.968
"I won't bore you
with the details.

38:13.968 --> 38:16.601
"But at this stage of the game,
I'll be lucky if I finish

38:16.601 --> 38:19.868
"this goddamn letter.

38:19.868 --> 38:21.467
"If it wasn't my ticker
that did me in,

38:21.467 --> 38:25.567
"please tell me I died
after eating 15 pizzas,

38:25.567 --> 38:28.801
"or during sex
with either multiple women

38:28.801 --> 38:29.934
or one really big one."

38:29.934 --> 38:31.667
[ALL CHUCKLE]

38:31.667 --> 38:34.000
"Either way that works for me.

38:34.000 --> 38:36.033
"But seriously,
I hope I went on the job

38:36.033 --> 38:38.634
"doing the work
I was meant to do

38:38.634 --> 38:40.434
"surrounded by you
and the guys.

38:41.901 --> 38:45.234
"Since it was
mostly about food with me,

38:45.234 --> 38:47.434
"I'm gonna leave you guys
with a recipe.

38:47.434 --> 38:52.033
"Take one self-absorbed
pretty-boy Puerto Rican.

38:54.934 --> 39:00.834
Add one 'long on attitude,
short on experience' black guy."

39:00.834 --> 39:02.701
[MAN CHUCKLES]

39:02.701 --> 39:05.133
"Then add two morons,

39:05.133 --> 39:08.601
"one more stupid than the other.

39:08.601 --> 39:09.834
[ALL CHUCKLING]

39:09.834 --> 39:11.767
"Mix together and let sit.

39:11.767 --> 39:16.334
"Then finally,
add one battle-scarred, haunted,

39:16.334 --> 39:18.601
"formerly drunken
Irish asshole,

39:18.601 --> 39:22.801
who screws up his life
like other people breathe."

39:22.801 --> 39:24.667
[CLEARS THROAT]

39:24.667 --> 39:26.601
"Blend all ingredients together,

39:26.601 --> 39:29.467
"turn on fire,
and hope for the best.

39:29.467 --> 39:31.367
"Sounds like shit, doesn't it?

39:31.367 --> 39:33.634
"Well, brother, I've tasted it.

39:33.634 --> 39:37.667
"I've eaten it up these last
few years, and it's delicious.

39:37.667 --> 39:39.801
"Okay, cornball, I know.

39:39.801 --> 39:44.133
"But you guys together,
you have something great.

39:44.133 --> 39:47.868
"Me being gone
doesn't change that.

39:47.868 --> 39:51.300
"Find yourself another
good-looking,

39:51.300 --> 39:53.934
"slightly overweight,
spoiler of women,

39:53.934 --> 39:55.767
"and you're back
at full strength.

39:55.767 --> 40:01.701
"Keep the crew together
and keep fighting the fight.

40:01.701 --> 40:05.868
"Don't worry about me, Tom.
I had a good life.

40:05.868 --> 40:08.234
"I knew brotherhood.

40:08.234 --> 40:11.334
"I knew being good
at something.

40:13.234 --> 40:15.968
"I knew what it meant
to have a friend.

40:15.968 --> 40:18.300
"Yeah, we had our ups and downs.

40:18.300 --> 40:22.701
"We're in a major down mode
at the moment, but with you,

40:22.701 --> 40:26.367
"the ups are good enough,
I'll take the downs.

40:26.367 --> 40:28.434
I love you, Tom."

40:28.434 --> 40:29.968
[CLEARS THROAT]

40:29.968 --> 40:33.968
"Not in that way.

40:33.968 --> 40:36.067
Okay, maybe a little that way."

40:36.067 --> 40:37.434
[ALL CHUCKLING]

40:37.434 --> 40:41.567
"I'll always be with you.
Your pal, Lou.

40:42.734 --> 40:43.934
"P.S. Don't forget

40:43.934 --> 40:46.667
"what the bagpipers
are supposed to play.

40:46.667 --> 40:48.067
"If you mess up,

40:48.067 --> 40:52.067
I promise I'll haunt you
forever, asshole."

40:55.400 --> 40:57.200
Anybody else?

41:04.734 --> 41:07.367
[PLAYING "IN-A-GADDA-DA-VIDA"]

41:12.734 --> 41:13.734
Is that--?

41:13.734 --> 41:16.734
"In-A-Gadda-Da-Vida,"
yeah.

41:16.734 --> 41:17.801
That's what he wanted.

41:41.000 --> 41:43.501
[GRUNTS]

41:46.400 --> 41:48.434
What?

41:48.434 --> 41:49.534
What the hell was
that?

41:49.534 --> 41:54.534
Just me throwing the...

41:54.534 --> 41:55.634
ashes.

41:55.634 --> 41:57.767
I've done this.
Those ain't ashes.

41:59.267 --> 42:01.267
You don't wanna know.
Seriously.

42:08.667 --> 42:10.400
Is that chocolate?

42:10.400 --> 42:12.701
Well, Lou did eat
a lot of chocolate.

42:12.701 --> 42:14.067
Tom.

42:14.067 --> 42:16.100
It's Duncan Hines
Red Velvet Cake Mix.

42:16.100 --> 42:17.467
We had an accident
on the way up.

42:17.467 --> 42:19.400
We had to pad Lou out
a little bit.

42:19.400 --> 42:21.801
Chocolate cake mix
was the best you could do?

42:21.801 --> 42:23.367
Jesus Christ.

42:23.367 --> 42:24.701
What?
Ashes are gray.

42:24.701 --> 42:26.734
I know ashes are gray.
You don't have to tell me.

42:26.734 --> 42:29.300
You don't think I looked for
gray food? There's no gray food.

42:29.300 --> 42:31.934
There's no gray food
in that store.
They don't make gray food.

42:31.934 --> 42:34.567
Can--? Never mind.

42:34.567 --> 42:37.501
Let's just get the hell
out of here.

42:37.501 --> 42:40.734
Between the heat,
the water and cake mix,

42:40.734 --> 42:44.000
you have a Betty Crocker
of a tidal wave in no time.

42:47.667 --> 42:50.834
[BAND CONTINUES PLAYING]

42:50.834 --> 42:55.934
Uhh... End of the road,
huh, Tom?

42:55.934 --> 42:58.234
Yep.
Yeah.

43:10.834 --> 43:15.868
Not sure what he meant
by "long on attitude,"

43:15.868 --> 43:18.067
but I'm gonna miss Lou.

43:25.734 --> 43:27.734
Hey, pal.
Hey.

43:29.834 --> 43:32.601
Yeah. I gotta tell you.

43:32.601 --> 43:34.300
Should have gone
with the fluffy yellow

43:34.300 --> 43:36.400
instead of the red velvet.
Big mistake, you know.

43:36.400 --> 43:39.100
Huge mistake. Really.

43:39.100 --> 43:41.133
It's not a good time?

43:41.133 --> 43:42.901
Yeah. I got it.

43:47.434 --> 43:48.901
[SOBS]

43:48.901 --> 43:50.400
All right.

43:50.400 --> 43:52.067
[CLEARS THROAT]

43:52.067 --> 43:54.000
Hey. Hey, kid.

43:54.000 --> 43:55.601
All right.

43:55.601 --> 43:56.901
[SIGHS]

44:02.901 --> 44:04.901
All right. Let's just...

